    "title": "All highlight / focus colour in Firefox should be the same in every version of Android", 
    "comments": [
        {
            "date": "2012-01-04 11:06:25", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Every highlight should a Firefox specific colour not the Android skin default colour for 2 reasons:\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "1. Maintain a consistent Firefox identity between platforms\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "2. There is conflict in highlight colours between android manufacturer skins and android OS colours: ie. On HTC 2.3 devices green is used for some highlights and orange (2.3 default highlight colour) is used in other places.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "The highlight used should be a gradient of #ff9500 > #e66000 If a gradient cannot be specified please us #f27a00\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Patryk Adamczyk (UX)", 
            "email": "Patryk Adamczyk (UX)"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2012-01-04 11:07:46", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This would apply to the following elements:\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "+ URL Bar focus border\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "+ List selection\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "+ Thumbnail selection\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "+ Tab menu (including \"active tab\" image)\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Patryk Adamczyk (UX)", 
            "email": "Patryk Adamczyk (UX)"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2012-01-05 10:45:03", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "not sure about this at all!\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "the highlight color of the browser should be consistent with every other application. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " lets not stand out, right?\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Doug Turner (:dougt)", 
            "email": "Doug Turner (:dougt)"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2012-01-05 11:07:35", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "On Android there is little consistency between the devices. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "On many devices you'll see atleast 2 colours. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "For instance: \n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "+ On ICS devices you'll see ICS blue and Gingerbread Orange. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "+ On skinned devices ie HTC. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "You'll see HTC green and Gingerbread Orange.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Some higher profile apps like Dolphin browser use a mix of green and native ICS blue.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Twitter uses a custom blue. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "etc.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I am pushing for a cohesive user experience on firefox properties where it feels like its a premium stand alone app not an assembly of native components, that's why we skinned the app with our own aesthetic and not copied ICS / gingerbread design.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Also since our properties tend to use silver / blues the orange really stands out creating a high visual accordance on what has been clicked / interacted with. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " The ICS blue has far too little contrast. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Not to mention the orange enforces the firefox brand identity. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Also if Android decides to use a blue - silver as a highlight in the next release we'd have to redesign the entire app since it would be invisible against our skin. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This would allow use to have some more independence from future Android visual design which changes frequently.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Patryk Adamczyk (UX)", 
            "email": "Patryk Adamczyk (UX)"
        }, 
